commit_message:
Ensure Puppet can run even on PoC net setups

For `puppet apply` to run successfully, outputs of `hostname -f` and
`facter fqdn` must match. In a properly configured network environment
the outputs should always match, in PoC environment they might not. This
patch overrides the FQDN fact to the result of `hostname -f`, which will
make `puppet apply` succeed even in PoC environments where DNS is not
configured properly.

Change-Id: I0d63fb0b862f984a196ac01345c74b4e5378e8a8
Partial-Bug: #1447497

commit_message:
Updated YAQL requirement to >= 0.2.6

YAQL has been update to pin ply requirement and a new version has been
released. This patch updates murano requirements to use this version.

Closes-bug: #1448990
(cherry picked from commit fbdf47eefbf2e8680704173e69aefdd6ac97e2b0)

Change-Id: I083720156d323a999740609e8c04b963c2eca043

commit_message:
Set external roles to import into ansible namespace

This patch sets the ansible external roles to export into the ansible
namespace (/etc/ansible/roles) instead of the os-ansible-deployment namespace.

This ensures a seperation of concerns and simplifies the os-ansible-deployment
upgrade process.

Partially implements: blueprint master-kilofication
Change-Id: I96dd61a4d3bdc52ae577fbf006387ffac58b7875
(cherry picked from commit 8bf181ebf184ba6e8d3efcd3e191cdcdd17a8c12)

commit_message:
Added check to see if the variable file is empty

The `pw-token-gen.py` script will fail if used against an empty file.
This change adds a None type check and returns an exit error and
messaage if the loaded value is None.

Closes-Bug: 1446338
Change-Id: I83cb9d1ef312f870f555c6de5f42815ba40e895e

commit_message:
Use IP address from 2nd admin net for boot via PXE

In tests for multiple cluster networks we configure 2nd
admin network interface on master node in order to
bootstrap slaves from non-default nodegroup. When we use
IP from default admin network for PXE nodes from 2nd
nodegroup fail to boot (due to new firewall NAT rules),
so changing boot host to IP from 2nd admin network.

Change-Id: Iee8d349877eb93bfe2627c54efd28c17f629db93
Closes-bug: #1448978

commit_message:
Install repos in HostSystem upgrader

Currently, the OpenStack upgrader copies repos to '/var/www/nailgun',
but before copying it checks whether they are installed or not and if
they do - removes them in order to make clear installation.

That cause issues when HostSystem upgrader creates 'Auxiliary' repos
and then OpenStack upgrader removes them as a part of repos
installation. In order to prevent that smeared logic about repos
installation, let's move it all to HostSystem upgrader.

Required-For: Ic68f19c7f6bb68a04fb5cc457dae7f92c1faacf2
Related-Bug: #1446075

Change-Id: I56e64e44786bcf08f83fc62ff59af747192e2470
Signed-off-by: Igor Kalnitsky <igor@kalnitsky.org>

Objects: Fix instance.system_metadata tracking

This fixes tracking of system_metadata where setting a system_metadata

commit_message:
Use keystoneclient to get endpoint if it's empty

We used to rely on keystoneclient code to get the proper endpoint from
keystone if it was not provided in the command line or as an
environment variable. This changed in a recent commit. So now that we
are using an adapter for the keystone sessions, we use the function
provided by that adapter.

Change-Id: I927a105831642d4fb00691ea2a97e27e79ebc7fd
Closes-Bug: #1443436

commit_message:
Make script executable and BSD sed compatible

This patch sets the sources-branch-updater script to be executable and adjusts
the in-place sed operation to work for both GNU sed and BSD sed.

Partially implements: blueprint master-kilofication
Change-Id: Ic2cd6a3a6a25d590c9cdbae8026dc3c4d5d5674d
(cherry picked from commit 28a2de8204b26307e35696413ba925bc67cceb49)

commit_message:
Added check to see if the variable file is empty

The `pw-token-gen.py` script will fail if used against an empty file.
This change adds a None type check and returns an exit error and
messaage if the loaded value is None.

Closes-Bug: 1446338
Change-Id: I83cb9d1ef312f870f555c6de5f42815ba40e895e
(cherry picked from commit 03646d48f358369a149e88cbdd800c285afec5bf)

commit_message:
utils: create_cow_image: Cleanup outdated comments

Confirmed this after an IRC conversation (because the pastebin linked in
the comment expired) with Joshua Harlow, who wrote the said comment.

Reasoning behind the comment "This doesn't seem to get inherited" is
that many moons ago when creating a qcow2 overlay based on a base image,
apparently, the overlay didn't inherit the 'cluster_size' from the
parent image. It's not the case any more as of today:

  $ qemu-img create -f qcow2 base.qcow2 1G
  Formatting 'base.qcow2', fmt=qcow2 size=1073741824 encryption=off cluster_size=65536 lazy_refcounts=off

  $ qemu-img create -f qcow2 -b ./base.qcow2 -o backing_fmt=qcow2 overlay1.qcow2
  Formatting 'overlay1.qcow2', fmt=qcow2 size=1073741824 backing_file='./base.qcow2' backing_fmt='qcow2' encryption=off cluster_size=65536 lazy_refcounts=off

The 'cluster_size' of the base and overlay images match.

So, remove the TODO item and the URL to expired pastebin.

PS: Please, let's not add pastebins in code -- they expire. If we're
referring to some content from random websites, at least a concise
summary should be noted in the commit message for permanent archival.

Change-Id: I43c0d8b4ac88ddc0899dbd1a5544edc76ef95ce9

commit_message:
Correct APT pinning

In order to set corrent pinning, we have to use repo's metadata and
that means download repo's Release file, parse it and create pinning
based on it. In that case we'll use all available pinning rules, so
all possible issues will be up to repo maintainer and not because
we're using error prone approach.

Port-Of: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/175358/

Co-Authored-By: Igor Kalnitsky <ikalnitsky@mirantis.com>
Related-Bug: #1438783

Change-Id: I71f2b72d914a39bbdf3f094e6b8fdd407fdc725b

commit_message:
Extract cloud-init-hosts element from core element

Extract /etc/hosts management from the core element into its own
element. Removal of this logic from the core element will happen in a
separate commit -- to keep the gate passing after each commit, we'll
need to first do a change to tripleo-ci and tripleo-incubator to use
this element.

Change-Id: I7b9862d19e25fd601aefd20a66bc37bf435e6364
Partial-Bug: #1447497

commit_message:
Remove duplicated l3 router scheduler test cases

Turn L3SchedulerTestCase to a mixin to reduce the number of
duplicated test cases.  There's no reason to run them in both
of L3SchedulerTestCase and L3ChanceSchedulerTestCase.

Closes-Bug: #1436164
Change-Id: Iee33f77fa2f9b9e20bb9c3fc4fb11a38de14bca5

commit_message:
Do not deploy 6.0.x releases

After upgrading to Fuel 6.1 the old releases have to be not available
for deployment new clusters, only for managing old ones. This patch
set 'is_deployable=False' to 6.0.x releases.

Closes-Bug: #1448176

Change-Id: Ieddddf10b2304037c10f5ea45540626cabb4e6f4
Signed-off-by: Igor Kalnitsky <igor@kalnitsky.org>

commit_message:
Clean up migration scripts

Since this is the first relase of MidoNet plugin with DB migration
scripts, and no one is using the DB, to prepare for the Kilo
release, clean up the scripts by re-organizing them properly.

Change-Id: I0199738d70e8984635c25e59afca112c8aae0151

commit_message:
CLI support to display DVR host mac

This commit implements CLI list and show commands to display
mac address address associated with each DVR host

Change-Id: Ibc84a84e3593652f4072a79ab34aa781038e0f3f
Implements: blueprint cli-dvr-host-mac

commit_message:
Set fixed version in containers' supervisor confs

Currently, containers' supervisor configs don't have the Fuel version
in the command line. It means that when supervisor tries to start a
container its version retrieved on fly from the '/etc/fuel/version.yaml'.
Since Fuel 6.1, the '/etc/fuel/version.yaml` has to be new, because
otherwise the 'host-upgrade.pp' will use incorrect current version.
Unfortunately, if '/etc/fuel/version.yaml' is new and the puppet
upgrades Docker package, the Docker containers will be stopped and
they won't up again because 'detecting container version on fly' will
give us wrong result (e.g. 6.1 instead of 6.0). So, the only thing
we can do is to set fixed container version in supervisor's configs,
so it won't rely on current state of '/etc/fuel/version.yaml'.

Required-For: Ic68f19c7f6bb68a04fb5cc457dae7f92c1faacf2
Related-Bug: #1446075

Change-Id: I1a32827952fcfbe705f37f46df3e80f6c4dc8bb3
Signed-off-by: Igor Kalnitsky <igor@kalnitsky.org>

commit_message:
Update pkg-map to reflect Ceph packages split on RHEL

Ceph packages have been split on RHEL as suggested by [1] but not
in EPEL nor in Fedora yet; this change updates the pkg-map(s) to
reflect the changes.

1. http://tracker.ceph.com/issues/10587

Change-Id: Ia067858c640af60c17d066fd1eeb43f3c82456f5

commit_message:
Add test templates for topology template

The templates is used for testing topology template functions. They
contain most of the features provided by topology template. But still
need improvement as the development of the TOSCA spec going on.
subsystem.yaml is used to test elements in topology template.
system.yaml is used to test substitution mapping. For it is not well
defined currently, it will be implemented later.
definition.yaml provides definitions required by the above two files.

partially implements: bp tosca-topology-template

Change-Id: I73006bb2880a69d20b647db750d806c87d0edfeb

commit_message:
Fix spec tests for RSpec 3.x and Puppet 4.x

Remove value test for ldap/project_filter and
ldap/project_attribute_ignore (the value is undef), and the comportment
is different between puppet3.x and puppet4.x (.with_value(nil) and
.with_value('')).

This patch also update RSpec 3.x matcher in order to remove deprecation
warnings (in unit spec/unit/provider/keystone_spec.rb).

Closes-bug: #1447620
Change-Id: Ib7118375d2ef72de045ece515fa611bdd3dda8e4

Currently a HA router can be successfully created even when
there is no enough active l3 agent. Current code only checks
existing l3 agents but not checking if the agent is already
down.

This patch fixes this problem by checking only active l3 agents
when getting the number of agents for scheduling HA router.

Closes-Bug: 1420117

commit_message:
Not creating HA router when not enough l3 agents

Currently a HA router can be successfully created even when
there is not enough active l3 agent. Current code only checks
existing l3 agents but does not check if the agent is already
down.

This patch fixes this problem by checking only active l3 agents
when getting the number of agents for scheduling HA router.

Closes-Bug: 1420117

Change-Id: I6c1d108db1a7c93b61c0dd0b1ffee319a411b17a

commit_message:
Ensure scaling limitation check will always be done

Currently, when count parameter is directly provided to action
when webhook is triggered, the size limitation check in
ScalingPolicy will be skipped. This is incorrect. This patch
makes ScalingPolicy check the size limitation based on count
parameter if it is provided.

Change-Id: Ia30ca829a1c86204721f9202bf0eb36942b25919
Closes-Bug: #1448960

commit_message:
Updated install.rst to follow doc conventions

changed service and project names per doc conventions
when referring to the services, use Compute
Image Service and Identity instead of nova glance
and keystone
changed horizon to lowercase throughout doc
http://wiki.opensstack.org/wiki/Documentation/Conventions
Partial-bug: 1446253

Change-Id: I5f3d8a086b38860bb77e6e71e91714fd49f5e1c6

commit_message:
client retrieval of freezer api endpoint

The api client queries keystone to obtain the freezer api endpoint,
provided that the freezer api service and endpoint have been registered in
keystone.

An optional parameter to specify the api endpoint is supported

Change-Id: I6626a60d1fd5d18a59376165e94c789832865ae0
Implements: blueprint freezer-apiclient-endpoint

commit_message:
Jshint unused and undef cleanup for D3 JS

Removing unused and undefined variables in D3 javascript.
This ensures that once we enable it globally, the gate will not barf.

Change-Id: I054bdd17d32c26b21fb0aba4656aef61c81c9d66
Partial-bug: #1438620

commit_message:
Moves trusted filter unit tests into own file

Breaks out trusted filter unit tests into their own file. In the
process, we remove all DB accesses from the unit tests and uncruft the
unit tests with mock.

(cherry picked from commit f388ac5e8f5338fd2c4817de11b7436f85036bc6)

Conflicts:
	nova/tests/scheduler/test_host_filters.py

Backporting this patch for
change I1ad57b5bd1986360416948fd00dec22456dc29a7 .

Added nova/tests/scheduler/filters/__init__.py, which is created by a
patch we aren't pulling in.

Updated test to use timeutils from nova.openstack.common instead of
oslo.utils, as the filter hasn't been updated yet to use oslo.utils.

(cherry picked from commit 54e099c4cde73461d4ab40a79eb24ed18177456e)

Conflicts:
	nova/tests/scheduler/test_host_filters.py

Removed test_trusted_filter_trusted_and_locale_formated_vtime_passes,
as we haven't backported change
Ic7351e0463c014321bdb4fcfeba90ac51460b325 .

Change-Id: Ic895b06a9f6a224f153f12ca5ab54dc8be931f13

commit_message:
Add support for customized cluster name

Current RBD driver assumes ceph cluster name to be 'ceph', for
cluster has a different name, the driver won't be able to connect
to the cluster.  This change add a new config option
'rbd_cluster_name' to address this issue.

DocImpact

Change-Id: I02ae1a255fd613fce291cc7ddf90cfd9175255a8
Closes-bug: #1444855
(cherry picked from commit 6db57c53a1363ff267e58f88b0937cd5d0e842c4)

commit_message:
RBD: Add missing Ceph customized cluster name support

It turns out '--cluster' is also needed when RBD driver talks to
ceph cluster using 'ceph' command (not via librados).  This change
appends RBDDriver._ceph_args with '--cluster' when 'rbd_cluster_name'
config option is not None.

Change-Id: Ie957a3658a630947a140f4172f775e42b7611c6e
Closes-bug: #1444855
(cherry picked from commit 877c8e7d8c0d397021e1a06b2d2a36962d6a9d42)

commit_message:
Replace BaseLinuxTestCase by BaseSudoTestCase

BaseLinuxTestCase provides 2 methods which are used once/three time(s),
this change inlines these methods and removes BaseLinuxTestCase and
replaces it by BaseSudoTestCase.

Change-Id: I2b60abf55193f535fc7d7637bcb2f15c6a372a87

commit_message:
Remove redundant code from VNX Cinder Driver

The logic on read-only volume in cinder/volume/drivers/emc/emc_vnx_cli.py
is duplicate to the logic in cinder/volume/manager.py. This patch is to
remove it.

Change-Id: Ib1a740a6065dbc8f3412d9dcf2e0d9025ab32d87
Closes-Bug: #1439531

commit_message:
Clean up targetcli ramdisk installation

The targetcli element was triggering a bunch of errors from dracut
when we installed all of Python.  It turns out this is because there
were filenames with spaces in the find output and the loop didn't
handle that properly.  This switches to a while loop that can
handle odd filenames.

commit_message:
Fixed issue with mismatched config in VMAX driver

When the source and target volumes have different meta device
configurations, clone volume will fail. This patch fixed the
problem.

Closes-Bug: #1442376
Change-Id: If2f2c085596b0045d7af6762bddeb4cd59158a57

commit_message:
Enable use of filter_function in PureISCIDriver

Adding filter_function to capabilities of PureISCIDriver.  Return
total_volumes as well for use with filter_function.

This will open a way for admins to prevent Cinder from scheduling
volumes on a Pure backend once it has reached the array’s limits. The
primary use case for this is volume limits. An example of a
filter_function that will prevent this issue would be:

filter_function="capabilities.total_volumes < 500”

This will prevent any issues with Purity versions that are limited to
500 volumes.

Without that filter_function the scheduler will continue to try and
schedule volume creation if space is available instead of selecting
another backend. The end result would be volume creation fails and the
volume is in an error state even though there are backends available
that could have handled it.

DocImpact: This means the PureISCSIDriver will now respect the
filter_function config option. Special Pure specific fields to filter
off of need to be added to the driver config manual.

Change-Id: I1368b74f79eb8c8560cf86df27f9af9541963a87
Closes-Bug: 1437082

[{'created': '2015-04-18 00:20:44.000000000', 'message': "Remove backward compatibility for check_is_admin

This routine in policy.py used to have a backward compatibility
check to ensure proper behaviour even when the policy.json file
did not have a specific 'context_is_admin' policy.
However, this backward compatibility check does not work anymore.
Quite worryingly when the 'context_is_admin' policy is not in
the policy.json file the enforce always evaluates a TrueCheck.
As a consequence not having context_is_admin in policy.json can
be dangerous. However, since Havana policy.json is shipping with
this policy.

Therefore this patch:
- Removes the backward compatibility check, since it does not work
- Fails, for safety, check_is_admin if 'context_is_admin' policy is
  not specified
- Fixed check_is_advsvc in the same way (the backward compatibility
  check never made any sense in this case)
- Fixes unit tests adding appropriate tests for check_is_admin and
  check_is_advsvc

This routine in policy.py used to have a backward compatibility
check to ensure proper behaviour even when the policy.json file
did not have a specific 'context_is_admin' policy.
However, this backward compatibility check does not work. It
appears indeed that it has been broken for several release cycles;
it is also possible that actually it never worked.
When the 'context_is_admin' policy is not in the policy.json file
the enforcer simply ends up evaluating whatever is the default
policy configured there.

Therefore this patch:
- Removes the backward compatibility check, since it does not work
- Fails, for safety, check_is_admin if 'context_is_admin' policy is
  not specified
- Fixeds check_is_advsvc in the same way (the backward compatibility
  check never made any sense for this function)
- Fixes unit tests adding appropriate tests for check_is_admin and
  check_is_advsvc

Closes-Bug: #1445690
"}]
commit_message:
Remove backward compatibility for check_is_admin

This routine in policy.py used to have a backward compatibility
check to ensure proper behaviour even when the policy.json file
did not have a specific 'context_is_admin' policy.
However, this backward compatibility check does not work. It
appears indeed that it has been broken for several release cycles;
it is also possible that actually it never worked.
When the 'context_is_admin' policy is not in the policy.json file
the enforcer simply ends up evaluating whatever is the default
policy configured there.

Therefore this patch:
- Removes the backward compatibility check, since it does not work
- Fails, for safety, check_is_admin if 'context_is_admin' policy is
  not specified
- Fixeds check_is_advsvc in the same way (the backward compatibility
  check never made any sense for this function)
- Fixes unit tests adding appropriate tests for check_is_admin and
  check_is_advsvc

Change-Id: Ia47e5781d86a3f21b9d837c9ac70a62ac435d20b
Closes-Bug: #1445690

commit_message:
Use hypervisor hostname for compute trust level

In XenAPI, service hostname and compute node hostname is different
because the Nova compute service may run in a separated VM and is
different with the hostname of the compute node.

The remote attestation service use the compute node's hostname because
it's the compute node that will run the servers.

(cherry picked from commit 3c88fce604959a68f48d71274e0d93b74da17e34)

Conflicts:
	nova/scheduler/filters/trusted_filter.py
	nova/tests/scheduler/test_host_filters.py

Closes-Bug: #1223452
Change-Id: I9a7ce74d595531196804615a8947e253b0bd3f1a

commit_message:
Fix keyerror issue when create baymodel

When we create a baymodel with a image which didn't set the os_distro
property, an keyerror will be occurred.

This patch fix this issue.

Change-Id: I61f35da599df95dcc8ed250a052b815152098122
Closes-Bug: #1448907

new cluster architecture, not the API plugin architecture.

revisions:
[{'created': '2015-04-24 17:16:25.000000000', 'message': 'Revert "L3 DB: Defer port DB subnet lookups"

This seems to have broken DVR

This reverts commit 9701bd479529ccc243e48fdb944c284d2921c376.

Change-Id: I32054ff00bf6992c5dedd21735b6d2afd15c5fb3
'}, {'created': '2015-04-24 17:52:36.000000000', 'message': "Add missing interface to populate subnets method

Change Ib46f685d72eb61ecbaa2869e28fb173cd6d49552 introduced
and optimization to defer the lookup of interface subnet info
until all of the router interfaces were collected. However,
it didn't add the DVR SNAT interface to the list of interfaces
to populate subnet info so it broke DVR.

This patch corrects the behavior by adding the DVR SNAT interface
to the list of ports that need subnet info populated.

commit_message:
Add missing interface to populate subnets method

Change Ib46f685d72eb61ecbaa2869e28fb173cd6d49552 introduced
and optimization to defer the lookup of interface subnet info
until all of the router interfaces were collected. However,
it didn't add the DVR SNAT interface to the list of interfaces
to populate subnet info so it broke DVR.

This patch corrects the behavior by adding the DVR SNAT interface
to the list of ports that need subnet info populated.

Change-Id: I32054ff00bf6992c5dedd21735b6d2afd15c5fb3

commit_message:
Jshint unused and undef cleanup for quota JS

Removing unused and undefined variables in quota javascript.
This ensures that once we enable it globally, the gate will not barf.

Change-Id: I1a6916607b7ef5af8bf6b459dbf8c4b438a1ac51
Partial-bug: #1438620

commit_message:
VMware: Ensure compute_node.hypervisor_hostname is unique

The VMware driver currently identifies a hypervisor as:

  <mo_id>(<cluster name>)

Cluster name is not unique, and mo_id is only unique in the scope of a
single vCenter, so the above can produce duplicate names when managing
clusters with the same name in multiple vCenters. This is especially
likely to occur in lab setups.

This change alters the above format to the following, which uniquely
identifies a cluster globally:

  <mo_id>.<vCenter uuid>

Closes-bug: #1329261
Co-Authored-By: Kanagaraj Manickam <kanagaraj.manickam@hp.com>
Change-Id: I2f3b5d224cc653d0465598de0788116e71d1ca0d

commit_message:
Fix bug when using --log-level option

Fixes a bug when using the --log-level/-o option. These are currently not
usable, because a condition always exits if there are not exactly two
command-line arguments used (the ip and port).

This patch also ensures that the used log-level settings are valid choices.

Change-Id: I5d64e57b59947c059924fce3e458cfe9fa284318

commit_message:
New consistency group APIs

In Kilo, two new APIs were added to support consistency groups
in Cinder:
* Modify consistency groups.
* Create consistency group from a snapshot of a consistency group.
This patch adds documentation for the new APIs.

Closes-Bug: 1362882

Change-Id: Ibf9c5dcb5726cea470c5874542ea4df19933179c

commit_message:
Fixed nova-network dhcp-hostsfile update during live-migration

During live migration _post_live_migration and
post_live_migration_at_destination_method are executed
simultaneously, because second one is called over rpc.cast
In _post_live_migration method there was setup_network_on_host
call with teardown=True, which expects new host in instances
table db field. This update could be happened later, as it
executes on destination node in second method. To guarantee
execution order  setup_network_on_host call, which cleans
dhcp-hostfile is moved to destination node.
Closes-Bug: #1444497

Change-Id: I55f0c0148c937601e78f0beecc21b30a1164a690

commit_message:
Merge V2 and V2.1 networks functional tests

Currently v2 and v2.1 have separate functional tests and their
corresponding sample files. As v2 and v2.1 are supposed to be identical,
there is overhead to maintain two set of functional tests and sample files.
We can have one set of tests which can run for both v2 and v2.1.

This commit merges networks functional tests.
Below APIs tests are megred-
-os-networks
-os-extended-networks
-os-networks-associate

Change-Id: I0fe9d82d5f847fb3fd3f231ccdc29d646d0ee0a3

commit_message:
Share V2 and V2.1 images functional tests

Currently v2 and v2.1 have separate functional tests and their
corresponding sample files. As v2 and v2.1 are supposed to be identical,
there is overhead to maintain two set of functional tests and sample files.
We can have one set of tests which can run for both v2 and v2.1.

This commit merges all images functional tests.
- images
- image_metadata
- image_size

Change-Id: I26bd1c521cb50c97a8720438fe08412577ae7204

Fix destroy of a LPAR that is missing on the host

Added exception logic to handle the case where the LPAR
that is the target of a destroy operation may not be on
the host.

[{'created': '2015-04-23 14:42:41.000000000', 'message': "sync oslo: service child process normal SIGTERM exit

service.py had some code where the child process would catch the
SIGTERM from the parent just so it could exit with 1 status rather
than with an indication that it exited due to SIGTERM. When
shutting down the parent doesn't care in what way the child ended,
only that they're all gone, so this code is unnecessary.

"}]
commit_message:
sync oslo: service child process normal SIGTERM exit

service.py had some code where the child process would catch the
SIGTERM from the parent just so it could exit with 1 status rather
than with an indication that it exited due to SIGTERM. When
shutting down the parent doesn't care in what way the child ended,
only that they're all gone, so this code is unnecessary.

Also, for some reason this caused the child to never exit while
there was an open connection from a client. Probably something
with eventlet and signal handling.

Syncs commit: 702bc569987854b602ef189655c201c348de84cb

Change-Id: I3c5249f5e59bb396bcb50964907ea61ebb2a3c8a
Closes-Bug: #1446583

commit_message:
FirstApp: Adjust conf.py

Sync conf.py with the way the openstack-manuals RST guides are setup.
The changed settings are needed for localization, PDF documents and bug
reporting.

Implements: blueprint openstack-firstapp

Change-Id: I0aed9f3c558d3cea3bb6e5a83bdeb7cf7f47a1bd

commit_message:
Remove downgrade support from the cellsv2 api db

The TC approved a cross project spec to stop putting db downgrade into
project migration repos:
https://github.com/openstack/openstack-specs/blob/master/specs/no-downward-sql-migration.rst
This was done after quite a bit of feedback from the operator community,
and everyone was good with it.

This implements that spec for Nova, adjust the tests to pass
accordingly, and changes the test which requires downgrade functions
to one that prohibits them.

Implements bp nova-no-downward-sql-migration

Change-Id: I972e1d79e570d57baac613e56570b49e1b1da28d

commit_message:
Add a conf-novanet to configure nova

Configure nova networking and nova quotas to allow 40 m1.small
instances to run.  Checks for keystone credentials set.  May only
be run once.

Change-Id: I36e01d42ec283651babbb59268452a65e644626e

Hi Haomeng, thanks for submitting this patch. I took a look at the bug. My opinion is that we should not be verifying/checking that an input value is UUID-like. The server already does this, and for the node, the value could be a UUID or a logical name.

The problem seems to be the GET call that is made, it doesn't include an object identifier so for eg node-show, the client sends a 'GET ../v1/nodes' instead of a 'GET ../v1/nodes/<identifier>'. It ends up making a node-list call instead. I think we should just change the client code to check that the identifier is non-empty or not blank spaces.

What do you think?"}, {'account_id': 8106, 'date': '2015-04-15 00:21:20.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 10: Workflow-1

Hi Ruby,

Agree with you, and let me change the validation logic to check if the input uuid is empty string or spaces.

Thanks for your comments.'}, {'account_id': 8106, 'date': '2015-04-16 03:13:44.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 11.'}, {'account_id': 14760, 'date': '2015-04-16 03:25:51.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 11: Code-Review+1

Hi Haomeng, I like your solution -- if we wanted to ensure that all arguments are not empty.

My concern though, is that there may be cases where it is OK for an argument to be empty, so I'm not convinced we want to do this.

For example (I didn't look at all the commands), "node chassis-create -d ''". That works w/o this change, but won't work with this change. Unless we think that this is a bug (and I don't think it is), we will have introduced a bug with this patch.

I think we might want to address this particular issue of preventing a *-show (eg node-show) from becoming a *-list.

What do you think?'}, {'account_id': 8106, 'date': '2015-04-16 23:58:46.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 13:

commit_message:
Ensure *-show input uuid is not empty

Ironic *-show does not ensure that uuid are not empty.

This patch adds checks to the client to ensure that command line
arguments are not empty strings or only whitespace. It will raise
a command exception if *-show command line argument is an empty
string or only whitespace.

Change-Id: Ia34957922006da5ecbbfc7483040d67ac51f0ada
Closes-Bug: 1442436

commit_message:
Fixed typo in cinder backup config

This changes the variable "cinder_backup_driver" to
"cinder_service_backup_driver" which will resolve the issue where the
backup service is unusable.

Change-Id: I53f61bda9693f5515334ae4b9555efc21768adc4
Closes-Bug: 1449004

commit_message:
Magic Search enhancements

Following updates to Magic Search.

- Switch to using fa-search, instead of fa-filter.
- Add one time data binding to static labels.
- Style MS box
- Corrected order of include in horizon.scss for
  /horizon/lib/magic_search/magic_search.scss
- Adds fa-server icon and lighter gray color  for server/api filter
- Adds fa-desktop icon for client side filter
- Optional: tooltip added to icons to help indicate visual difference.

Partially Implements: blueprint filtered-client-side-table

Change-Id: I543065a4e1219982539acd659e1e4164c2e053a9

commit_message:
changed heat dev docs to comply with conventions

With the incorporation of many projects within OpenStack, it's very important to
use standards in the documentation This is important for formalization as well
as consistency
the proper usage is: heat or Orchestration or Orchestration module
heat should not be capitalized
https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/Documentation/Conventions

Change-Id: Icbc213ecf2f564981e8a1595b5fc557d1b218f9c

I have a meta question. I think this was split from the original add/remove case because add is hard. The question is: if we decide not to do add, is remove really useful on its own? Is it going to be more confusing to users if they can remove things from a group that are still running, but can't add them? Right now, it's pretty symmetric. You get into a group at birth, and leave at death.

Could we at least document a use case where it makes sense to do this without add, if add never gets implemented/approved? Apologies if it has already been discussed somewhere else and I missed it."}, {'account_id': 7664, 'date': '2014-12-03 18:37:12.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 5:

Hey Dan, great question.  This was discussed a bit, albeit mostly verbally.  While it would be nice to have both remove and add, remove on its own can still be useful (and allows us to stage this to keep it simple).

An example use case would be:
- Admin deploys VM-1, VM-2, VM-3 in SG-A and specifies 'affinity' policy for performance reasons.
- Company buys an uber-fast 10GB switch, alleviating their initial performance concerns.
- Admin can now remove VM-3 from SG-A and put it on another machine to help free some resource capacity (this is better than having to delete VM-3 to remove it and re-deploy/configure the VM)."}, {'account_id': 4393, 'date': '2014-12-03 18:52:16.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 5:

Right, so the converse situation "justifies" add:

- Admin deploys VM-1 and VM-2
- Customer realizes that performance between these is bad, wants them co-located
- Admin adds them to an affinity group and hits migrate on one so they land together

I think that once you disassociate the group membership from the lifetime of a VM, then the user is going to be seriously confused about why they can remove but not add. That's why I think that the fate of remove and add should probably be tied together.'}, {'account_id': 7664, 'date': '2014-12-03 19:06:25.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 5:

Yep, it would be nice to have symmetry - and that's why the 'add' spec will be posted by Jennifer in the next few days.  That said, based on some discussions I had with jogo, johnthetubaguy and bauzas at the summit - we felt getting 'remove' done in Kilo was a good way to stage this, and still provide value-add over what an admin can do today.

I don't think the confusion the admin will have about why they can't add will outweigh not being able to remove at all, but that's just my $0.02 after discussion with several cloud admins.  :-)"}, {'account_id': 1849, 'date': '2014-12-04 13:11:23.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 5:

I agree with Dan that having remove and not add can be confusing. I also think that remove is significantly easier to implement then add. So perhaps we should think out how add would work and make sure its feasible (target post K), before approving this spec.

I am not too concerned about having remove and not add for a single cycle. But if we end up with just remove, that will be confusing.'}, {'account_id': 7664, 'date': '2014-12-04 13:53:29.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 5:

Thanks, jogo.  We'll be posting 'add' spec likely in the next day or so.  It should be feasible, but will likely take some iterating since there is more complexity as we discussed.  We will circle back with you once that's posted.  Thanks."}, {'account_id': 4393, 'date': '2014-12-04 16:00:16.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 5:

Joe, right, my point is that I think add is going to be really hard/contentious. I don't want to split these up because remove is easy and we want to schedule it for kilo, only to find out that we can't agree on an add implementation.

I also think that it's entirely possible that we could settle on a plan for add and find out that the implementation is not as straightforward as we expected. Thus, I would rather see them tied together from a planning POV. The patches to add the two functions can be separate, but I would hesitate to merge remove until we have settled on an add implementation.

Anyway, just MHO."}, {'account_id': 7221, 'date': '2014-12-05 00:11:02.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 5:

I have submitted the add spec for review:
https://review.openstack.org/139272'}, {'account_id': 7166, 'date': '2014-12-05 08:18:14.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 5:

Correct me if I'm wrong, but at the moment adding an instance to a group is implicit by asking for a group UUID when booting.

The main problem that operators would face is that they can rollback their previous decisions and leave written in the marble (eh, stone ;-)) their current topologies. Here, IMHO this spec, even if simplier to implement (because of no race conditions to manage) is still very valuable.

Waiting for another spec which would just extend the API for managing those sounds quite unfair, as it would delay the main feature that operators are wanting.

Anyway, as grealy said Dan, that's just MHO."}, {'account_id': 7664, 'date': '2014-12-09 03:20:10.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 5:

As Joe Gordon requested and previously mentioned by Jennifer, the spec for add has been posted.  While we understand add may not be accepted for Kilo (although we'd welcome it :), I hope you can see sufficient thought and detail has been posted in the spec such that we can minimally proceed with this (far simpler) remove spec for Kilo to make forward progress.

Thanks again!"}, {'account_id': 7221, 'date': '2014-12-11 16:04:32.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 6.'}, {'account_id': 7221, 'date': '2014-12-11 16:05:58.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 6:

Dan - https://blueprints.launchpad.net/nova/+spec/dynamic-server-groups-add is the add spec too.

How about we approve both of these (still naturally subject to code reviews) and make them conditional on each other?  It will allow the work to be split up nicely as well as advised by jogo and johnthetubaguy.

Otherwise, as I mentioned previously, I'm not sure why we are so worried about an admin getting "confused" about why you can remove, but not add.  I don't think the confusion will be any less than an admin wondering why s/he can't do either of these anyway and having to delete their VM.  Additionally, we do have the add spec (mentioned previously) with a lot of detail about how to implement it.

commit_message:
Imporve coverage job to make it voting

By default coverage job just generates cover directory with pretty HTML
report.

This change makes it voting:

It compares coverage of latest changes against that previous commit
and prints diff in case of adding new lines withou UT coverage.

As well it genereates HTML reports in cover/ dir

Change-Id: I1ac078ec67c92d0b8d6d3bb96f9ea79f61c5559a

commit_message:
glance provider: pick os_region_name from DEFAULT

In ::glance::api, os_region_name is set in DEFAULT which work for both
Juno & Kilo.

'glance_store' section has been introduced in Kilo which breaks Juno.
Until we decide our policy to manage master, let's use DEFAULT so both
releases work well.

Change-Id: I1c519146d3fe62f8c8fc8c2d85805db11af21e4c

I agree with the comments Valeriy has made in the previous patchset.  I actually authored the change that Valeriy linked to the post test hook.  I think I created that patch for the same reason you're stating here: we're reusing these files in our CI system internally to run against some of our own drivers.  These drivers don't all support both modes of operation and I needed a way to force the tests into either a multi-tenancy or single-tenancy run.  This can be done by adding an environment variable to your jenkins job:  http://paste.openstack.org/show/208468/"}, {'account_id': 11865, 'date': '2015-04-27 16:51:17.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-2

Given Andrew's comments, I remain unconvinced this change is needed and will await further input from Ramy."}, {'account_id': 9624, 'date': '2015-04-27 18:14:53.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

ok, making progress on my configuration. My tests were running twice' because I had export DEVSTACK_GATE_TEMPEST=1

Taking that out removes the 'first' set of tests, and now only the post-test-hook tests are run. However those tests fail with "Missing API credentials in configuration". 

I'm still a bit confused why this is a "post"-test-hook. Why are the settings not done during pre-test hook? 

Will leave this patch up a bit longer as WIP until I resolve my issues.'}, {'account_id': 9366, 'date': '2015-04-27 18:26:29.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

The tempest.conf file doesn't exist until after devstack runs.  pre_test_hook runs before devstack is setup, post_test_hook runs after devstack is setup.  So I put the changing of the configuration values in the post_test_hook so the conf files would already exist."}, {'account_id': 9624, 'date': '2015-04-27 21:16:40.000000000', 'content': "Abandoned

Worked with Andrew Kerr and got it working.
Gotcha's:
1. Don't export DEVSTACK_GATE_TEMPEST=1 in the job 
2. Manually export ENABLED_SERVICES=tempest

These are done in e.g. https://github.com/openstack-infra/project-config/blob/master/jenkins/jobs/manila.yaml#L65, so these are my misconfigurations. Abandoning."}]

commit_message:
Skip share tests when not supported by the driver

Although the driver states it doesn't support server shares
in the configuration file via the driver_handles_share_servers property,
they are still being executed and failing by tempest.

This issue is not being caught in the gate because the default driver
supports both modes. This change uses the job configuration to ensure both
settings are aligned for the tests run after the pre_test_hook is called
but before the post_test_hook is called.

According to the manila tempest configuration, the tempest.conf
also needs multitenancy configuration set to false so that they are skipped [1]

[1] https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/Manila/docs/HOWTO_use_tempest_with_manila#Option_.22multitenancy_enabled.22

Change-Id: I56c56d251982f7b687483fe380669a64c1b05e09

commit_message:
V2:cinder create --image option doesn't work

In create volume help, --image optional parameter is allowed to
be passed to create volume, but even after passing valid image ID
or NAME, volume is created without image.

Assigned image  parameter to the image_ref to fix this issue.

Closes-Bug: 1447589
Change-Id: I21b8a51451a2caf230ca04103b2d573d1aa966b4

(5 comments)

This spec reads more like a blog post of the different ways that IPv6 floating IPs can be supported, rather than a specification about what implementation is going to be chosen for development during kilo.

For example, there are at least two different ways (possibly even a third, although it's a little fuzzy) discussed in this blueprint for supporting IPv6 floating IPs, either through using radvd to send unicast RAs, but then also an implementation that would be stateful and use dnsmasq. I think we should probably pick a single implementation, create a spec for each that is something like "Support IPv6 floating IPs with radvd" - that will make it easier to review, as well as schedule work and track progress.'}, {'account_id': 13409, 'date': '2014-12-07 23:35:06.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

(11 comments)

The proposal looks good to me overall, but I have several questions/concerns and a few nits.'}, {'account_id': 4656, 'date': '2014-12-07 23:51:35.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

(9 comments)'}, {'account_id': 105, 'date': '2014-12-08 19:50:48.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review-2

I think we decided in Juno not to do floating IPs for IPV6, right?'}, {'account_id': 6685, 'date': '2014-12-09 03:57:40.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

(7 comments)

Hi Kyle, thanks for looking at it. I think the perception over ipv6 floatingip during that time was:
  -- ipv6 address is abundant, native ipv6 address/GUA can be used for tenant.
  -- floatingip should be implemented with NAT and NAT is not desirable for v6

as indicated in the spec, NAT is considered undesirable for IPv6 [RFC4864]_, but its deployment may be
likely in some cases [RFC5902]_. Therefore, NAT targets were introduced into linux ip6tables around 3.7. In addition, we can implement floatingip differently for ipv6 as described in the sepc. Third, I've heard strong options from the community on using the same floatingip API for v6 in the interest of using the same tooling already available for ipv4. 

Since floatingip is an integral part of the neutron router, I initially put it in the ipv6 router and DVR's spec. Some people suggested to separate it out. And I think it makes sense. Thus this new BP and spec."}, {'account_id': 6685, 'date': '2014-12-09 03:58:02.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 2.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-12-09 04:01:59.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Verified+1

commit_message:
Improve angular test dependency versions

Currently our angular test dependencies are pinned, and pinned rather
low.  I'd like to both increase the versions numbers and unpin the
version numbers.

npm allows some pretty cool version-number-controls:
https://docs.npmjs.com/files/package.json#dependencies

I claim that since we're dealing with dev-dependencies, we are more than
ok using the "^" or "~" syntax.

NOTE: karma-jasmine >= 0.3 requires a separate install of jasmine-core.

Also, upgrading the jasmine version will allow us to run a single
test-suite or test:
describe -> fdescribe
it -> fit

Change-Id: I38cf1df84635745bfb4001492baf563b7c112a35

commit_message:
Enable tracing option

Add -x option to enable tracing, much like what disk-image-create does.
All the -x specified are also passed directly to disk-image-create, to
enable tracing there too (and thus in elements).

Change-Id: I27ebf010b09add8ea99a997eb292e0b474f2ca66

Heartbeat is supported only with recent version
of kombu (>=3.0.7) and amqp (>=1.4.0)

commit_message:
Add introduction to OpenStack Networking section

Includes the definition of OpenStack Networking (neutron)
with its basic components and the type of networks
available

Change-Id: I9cdb57704df1255e274a0a17b30c28cad60d4be5
Partially-Implements: blueprint create-networking-guide

commit_message:
Add external genconfig calls

After moving to oslo.config we still were using
incubator config generator.  This was ok, but the
problem is we haven't been pulling config options
from the oslo libs.
This is a hack that just appends external lib calls
and appends those options to the sample file being built.

Closes-Bug: #1447380

Change-Id: Ie19083d2a94385526d8d2277565c5a6d83ced6f2

commit_message:
Fixed typo in cinder backup config

This changes the variable "cinder_backup_driver" to
"cinder_service_backup_driver" which will resolve the issue where the
backup service is unusable.

Closes-Bug: 1449004

Change-Id: I53f61bda9693f5515334ae4b9555efc21768adc4
(cherry picked from commit 677abdefdfb8cf2f710a28d1219d1406925f6e9b)

[{'created': '2015-04-24 11:39:05.000000000', 'message': "Don't resync on DHCP agent setup failure

There are various cases where the DHCP agent will try to
create a DHCP port for a network and there will be a failure.
This has primarily been caused by a lack of available IP addresses

commit_message:
Don't resync on DHCP agent setup failure

There are various cases where the DHCP agent will try to
create a DHCP port for a network and there will be a failure.
This has primarily been caused by a lack of available IP addresses
in the allocation pool. Trying to fix all availability corner cases
on the server side will be very difficult due to race conditions between
multiple ports being created, the dhcp_agents_per_network parameter, etc.

This patch just stops the resync attempt on the agent side if a failure
is caused by an IP address generation problem. Future updates to the subnet
will cause another attempt so if the tenant does fix the issue they will
get DHCP service.

Change-Id: I0896730126d6dca13fe9284b4d812cfb081b6218
Closes-Bug: #1447883
(cherry picked from commit db9ac7e0110a0c2ef1b65213317ee8b7f1053ddc)

commit_message:
Add HaproxyNSDriver to lbaas entry points

If neutron package is used in path for device_driver then agent fails to
start. This patch adds entry point for such driver.

Change-Id: I28e022ca0b07a5c4ba747ebad0d53db96ded83bf
Closes-Bug: 1441107
(cherry picked from commit 3665e0cc7b69e47d24b838aa6c91e007d16a71d1)

commit_message:
Add logic to pass sg and sg-rules to ODL

This commit adds a callback hook into the ODL MechanismDriver to handle
security-group and security-group-rules createn, update, and delete.

Closes-Bug: #1444112

Change-Id: I07ef8e0277a66294513693d011d4ef998ae134ec
Depends-On: Ifa1d7ee9c967576f824f1129dd68e6e3abd48f5c

'}, {'created': '2015-03-11 06:33:32.000000000', 'message': 'Delete the temporary volume if migration fails

Issues resolved in this patch include:
* A temporary volume is created on the destination host before migrating
the data from the source. However, if the creation of this volume fails,
its record will be left in the database as redundant information. This
patch will remove the database record if the creation fails.

* If attaching the src volme fails, in the exception hadling part we
need to detach the src volume not the dest volume. If attaching the dest
volume fails, in the exception handling part we need to detach the
dest volume.

closes-bug: #1398177

Change-Id: I5bc75bd7652841fddd66481ee001fb682168215c
'}, {'created': '2015-03-11 08:13:04.000000000', 'message': 'Delete the temporary volume if migration fails

Issues resolved in this patch include the following changes:
* A temporary volume is created on the destination host before migrating
the data from the source. However, if the creation of this volume fails,
its record will be left in the database as redundant information. This
patch will remove the database record if the creation fails.

* If attaching the remote dest volme fails at rpcapi.initialize_connection
due to timeout, we need to terminate the connection. Otherwise, the dest
volume will not be released and successfully deleted.

closes-bug: #1398177

Change-Id: I5bc75bd7652841fddd66481ee001fb682168215c

commit_message:
Delete the temporary volume if migration fails

Issues resolved in this patch include the following changes:
* A temporary volume is created on the destination host before migrating
the data from the source. However, if the creation of this volume fails,
its record will be left in the database as redundant information. This
patch will remove the database record if the creation fails.

* If attaching the remote dest volme fails at initialize_connection
due to timeout, we need to terminate the connection. Otherwise, the dest
volume will not be released and successfully deleted.

Closes-bug: #1398177
Change-Id: I5bc75bd7652841fddd66481ee001fb682168215c

commit_message:
networking-nec: add ability to create and manage branches

Enable the networking-nec-release team to create and manage branches.
For example we need to create stable/kilo branch in the near future.

Change-Id: I007b096fbdbcc478eeadab382058a56580327b63

commit_message:
[DO-NOT-MERGE] Enable libvirt debug logs and core dumps

This is to troubleshoot a libvirt error seen in the CI gate (on
CentOS7):

  "Caught Segmentation violation dumping internal log buffer"

With versions:

  libvirt-1.1.1-29.el7_0.7.x86_64
  qemu-system-x86-2.0.0-1.el7.3.x86_64

Change-Id: I1904ba9c9dd1ba73c0e064a3fd8abb098fc32870

commit_message:
Remove verbose option from rpmbuild

  rpmbuild verbose option generated very huge output.
  These output messages are useless, so they could be skipped

  Closes-bug: #1443496

Change-Id: Iedcde7d3a195d5037d17ae60fc5062ac362e6eb5

[{'created': '2015-04-20 20:40:33.000000000', 'message': 'Adds improved error code handling for pkcs11 errors returned from HSM.

The error returned by HSM is currently formated in decimal where as the actual pkcs11 error codes are hexidecimal. This change utilizes a dictionary of both the hexidecimal and string representation of the decimal to make errors easier to be researched and corrected.

Change-Id: I85b28e7ff28773d849b5ea71de3ef26d972de59d
Closes-Bug: #1445610

commit_message:
Improved error code handling for pkcs11 errors

Updated P11CryptoPluginException text to add hexidecimal and error code string

Added Localization to P11CryptoPluginException

Change-Id: I85b28e7ff28773d849b5ea71de3ef26d972de59d

[{'created': '2015-04-27 17:17:41.000000000', 'message': "Reduce number of services running in largeops-src

The largeops-src test is used for libraries that can break largeops
(oslo.messaging, oslo.db etc.) and is hitting mysql's connection limit
periodically.  Stop running services that large-ops doesn't test to
mitigate this.

Change-Id: I8ab0cee07cbc0649eda37b686a67b81a46586fcb
Partial-Bug: #1403284
"}]
commit_message:
Reduce number of services running in largeops-src

The largeops-src test is used for libraries that can break largeops
(oslo.messaging, oslo.db etc.) and is hitting mysql's connection limit
periodically.  Stop running services that large-ops doesn't test to
mitigate this.

Change-Id: I8ab0cee07cbc0649eda37b686a67b81a46586fcb
Partial-Bug: #1403284

commit_message:
moving from bundler to chefdk

 - updated Rakefile to use 'chef exec' instead of 'bundle exec'

 - added fauxhai permission workaround to bootstrap.sh

commit_message:
Switch all uses of urlparse to import from six

As part of enabling python3 support in tempest we need to be able to
handle urlparse usage in both python2 and python3. Six provies a compat
layer for doing this, so this commit moves all uses of urllparse to
get it through six.

Change-Id: Ic9c15d90fd3b8413fec4d01a070cc167f7536e62

commit_message:
Don't truncate osapi_volume_link prefixes

When osapi_volume_link_prefix is defined and used to update the
links return in API responses, do not drop the path component of
the overriding link prefix.

Change-Id: Ic84e16cdfa989d4af7f076a4c244808be2ca4dce
Closes-Bug: #1304099

commit_message:
add what-broke.py analayzer

This runs through all of global-requirements.txt and looks at the
release history of all components over the last N days, returning the
released list. This is helpful in unexplained gate breaks to at least
look for candidate libraries.

Fleshed out some docs to explain intent for future consumers /
modifiers of this script.

Change-Id: I5880a1d7f0a6063a45f7533319fed1ff56057144

commit_message:
L23network related fixes:

* l23network module initialization for granular deployment
* wrong bridge type while creating integration and tun bridge.
* bug/1446187

Note: After refactoring L23network module default provider
for bridges was changed from 'ovs' to 'lnx', but Neutron
requires 'ovs' bridges in any way.
Neutron no more need for creating br-int and br-tun
(upstream-bug: https://bugs.launchpad.net/puppet-neutron/+bug/1436422)

Change-Id: Ib28558f64111c967cfdd1b6ed1a2008b5767cb87
Closes-bug: #1440681
Closes-bug: #1446187
Closes-bug: #1447665
Closes-bug: #1447085
Closes-bug: #1448157

commit_message:
Make package 'bridge-utils' usage safe

When using puppet-nova with another big Puppet modules
this package may be defined before.

The solution is to make a definition safe.

Upstream-bug:  https://bugs.launchpad.net/puppet-nova/+bug/1445437

Fuel-CI: disable
Related-bug: #1440681
Change-Id: Ie1dc7c9d6b2b05802b38974d6303b41f035676ab

commit_message:
Don't lookup service url when bypass_url is given

Change https://review.openstack.org/#/c/164321 broke the bypass_url
option. It made the assumption that self.service_catalog won't be set
in novaclient/client.py when bypass_url is specified, which isn't
necessarily true. This change adds a check for self.bypass_url and
looks up service url only if bypass_url hasn't been specified.

Closes-Bug: #1445086

Change-Id: I72d2b3e3199aeae7fb2f2c68be259774e07a4501

commit_message:
[install-guide] Use the admin tenant to test heat

If nova-network is used, getting the network ID to run the heat example
stack requires admin rights. For simplicity, use the admin credentials
for both nova and neutron scenarios.

Change-Id: Ic2c5477154e608f94e8023e6d2a237d9879fc74b
Closes-Bug: #1437194

commit_message:
Replace "regionOne" with "RegionOne"

This fixes an inconsistency between the install guide
and other OpenStack components, which names the first region in Camel Case.

Change-Id: I80a1827e9008777e73dce1dd3a95ece5dd614744
Related-Change: I8f47be1b4b43defb86b4da2a34c5f40494361045

commit_message:
Enables os-access-ips extension

Also, removes obsolete 'access_ip_*' attributes
and removes obsolete attributes from api samples
Makes sure that all occurrences of "v3" are "v2.1"

Change-Id: I5146560e95d9b870cd6e9ebc71cdde923a080c6f
Closes-Bug: #1245804
Closes-Bug: #1242962
Closes-Bug: #1211191

commit_message:
Context data evaluation fixed

Fixed an issue when an empty list or a False boolean value was not
properly passed as the context data to the executor.

Cherry-picked from 
https://github.com/ativelkov/yaql/commit/e3e2e07603fc321a0dabed581356f58f7af80353

Change-Id: I0b44deba1c347c2d0680136a3f5bfc019447451f

commit_message:
Add other_networks to vrouter ns

- Remove host interface creation from ns_ntp ocf
- Create new crm resource vrouter that handles other_networks
- Update direct_networks.rb to parse custom routes

Change-Id: Iea26e1755e7e6d6310ad7cdb77ef1b21d850ff36
Closes-Bug: 1436868

commit_message:
Fix for missing id check in ACL count query.

Fixing issue and adding unit test to cover this API specifically.
It may need to be backported to Kilo as well.

Closes-Bug: #1447868

[{'created': '2014-08-08 13:31:48.000000000', 'message': 'Common alembic environment runner.

Alembic lib uses module named env.py to configure engine and run
migration scripts. `alembic_env` is an extendable/rewritable base class
for the same purposes. An ultimate project should provide `env.py` at
revisions directory. An `env.py` subclasses the provided base class and
call `run_migrations` method.

Implements: blueprint common-alembic-env
Change-Id: Id592961e4874e6b95cbfeb8e00308df20052f640
'}, {'created': '2014-10-07 09:06:53.000000000', 'message': 'Common alembic environment runner.

commit_message:
Common alembic environment runner.

Alembic lib uses module named env.py to configure engine and run
migration scripts. `alembic_env` is an extendable/rewritable base class
for the same purposes. An ultimate project should provide `env.py` at
revisions directory. An `env.py` subclasses the provided base class and
call `run_migrations` method.

Implements: blueprint common-alembic-env
Change-Id: Id592961e4874e6b95cbfeb8e00308df20052f640

commit_message:
Added branch creation to Magnum ACL

The ACL for magnum projibits the PTL from creating a branch. This
adjustment allows brach creation by members of the magnum-milestone
group.

Change-Id: I53e3caec9d594b31c8024d7cd5a8ed171439817f

(6 comments)

Unfortunately, this won't work out-of-box right now.

We still need to solve the problem with passing a custom Engine/Connection instance to alembic when running migration scripts (I had a chat with Mike on this yesterday on #openstack-oslo http://paste.openstack.org/show/85307/).

So basically we have 3 choices here:

1. Provide a common env.py, make consuming projects use it (neutron, ironic), tweak the test to use it.

2. Modify alembic to make it possible to run 'custom' env.py  (not the one provided by a consuming projects that lives right next to the migration scripts, but for which we can create a custom engine), release new version of alembic, modify global requirements, tweak the test.

3. Tweak the test, so that it provides callbacks to be overridden in subclasses (similar to https://review.openstack.org/#/c/93398/), so that we can ask the consuming projects to run the migration scripts against the db we need (this will require more work in consuming projects).

I'd go for the first choice, but this will probably take some time."}, {'account_id': 7536, 'date': '2014-07-03 15:32:16.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 14.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-07-03 15:32:17.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 14:

(3 comments)

I think moving to alembic is a big deal and it's hard to just add a few things to oslo.db without any context.   I'd really like to see a full-blown "this is how to use alembic" solution, where individual projects have a very small set of decisions to make, and oslo.db supplies the whole thing.  It is really enough of a concept that I'd even make it a new package oslo.migrations.   I think config should be totally designed, not use alembic.ini, and take in cfg.CONF and feed that into alembic's Config object, the runner should be openstack specific and build on top of alembic.config.CommandLine (this is a very extensible system now as we've had users build such systems), and anything else that needs to be made public API in alembic should be done so.

if we just provide a few helpers and not much direction, then every project is again going to invent all their own systems and we will have yet another all-over-the-place situation.   This is a much bigger deal in Openstack than people seem to realize.  Just that tests are written and configured dramatically differently between nova, keystone, and neutron as examples is a major issue.'}, {'account_id': 7536, 'date': '2014-07-24 11:44:36.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 28:

(3 comments)

I see your point and I agree with you. For now, I have a far from perfect but workable solution. I believe this big work with migrations and Alembic can't be done with the only one patch. I'll keep my research. If a people will decide to wait until this patch will contain a runner and common env.py (not template), I'm ok with it. If the patch will be merged, as it raw but usable, I'm ok with it too. I'll make several following patches, to make this solution all-sufficient and OpenStack specific."}, {'account_id': 7536, 'date': '2014-07-24 11:54:09.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 29.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-07-24 11:54:10.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 29:

(ie. keymap, server_listen, server_proxyclient_address)"}, {'account_id': 8482, 'date': '2014-11-19 18:37:47.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

Can you add a link to the documentation about the deprecated parameters in the commit message?'}, {'account_id': 8482, 'date': '2014-11-19 18:38:42.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

Oops, didn't see Yanis's comment"}, {'account_id': 11238, 'date': '2014-11-20 12:02:38.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

(1 comment)'}, {'account_id': 11238, 'date': '2014-11-20 12:42:41.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

There are 2 classes that configure spice. Keymap, server_listen and server_proxyclient_address are already in Nova::Compute::Spice. This is the config which is applied on the compute nodes. The second class, Nova::Spicehtml5proxy, configures the Spice HTML5 proxy and will be applied to a controller node. The second class still configured the parameters in [DEFAULT] which I corrected by my change.

As for the html5proxy_base_url vs. html5proxy_host/port, the html5proxy_base_url parameter is used by the compute node generate a URL for the proxy (what is returned by `nova get-spice-console someinstance spice-html5`) and is not used to configure the Spice proxy itself. I looked into the code of spicehtml5proxy.py (https://github.com/openstack/nova/blob/master/nova/cmd/spicehtml5proxy.py) and there the html5proxy_host and html5proxy_port are used. So this might be missing in the documentation of Nova.'}, {'account_id': 11238, 'date': '2014-11-24 09:06:20.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

See also: https://bugs.launchpad.net/openstack-manuals/+bug/1394595'}, {'account_id': 9410, 'date': '2014-11-24 17:51:26.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

(1 comment)

commit_message:
Moved spice configuration options from DEFAULT to spice section.

Configuration for spice now has a seperate section in nova.conf, moved
DEFAULT/spicehtml5proxy_host and DEFAULT/spicehtml5proxy_port to
spice/html5proxy_host and spice/html5proxy_port. Added spice/enabled and
spice/agent_enabled.

See also:
http://docs.openstack.org/admin-guide-cloud/content/spice-console.html
https://bugs.launchpad.net/openstack-manuals/+bug/1394595

Change-Id: If758377245fe5b8e06c3ee1afb0595beb90a5038

commit_message:
Implement wrapper for ascii table parser from tempest_lib.cli

Implement wrapper for ascii table parser from tempest_lib.cli
to parse manila specific output from console client in
functional tests.

Partially implements bp functional-tests

Couple of questions:

1) what would the changes in an application's use of oslo.log look like. Today we use logging.getLogger(__name__) kind of everywhere (in Nova for instance). How do you recommend specifying to the logger that we're the APP.

2) how does one turn on full debugging if they need it in an application? When one does that, how do you ensure iso8601 is not ever at DEBUG level.

3) how do we address the random connection pool WARN messages out of requests which scare people, but as far as I can tell are completely innocuous."}, {'account_id': 1736, 'date': '2015-04-14 10:42:36.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Code-Review+1'}, {'account_id': 2472, 'date': '2015-04-14 17:25:43.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

@Sean - 

1. The application tells oslo.log its name through the "product_name" argument to oslo_log.log.setup(), so we already know the name. I don't anticipate any application-level code changes to enable the features described here.

2. For full debugging, do you mean also oslo libraries or *all* libraries? We could change the default level for oslo when the debug flag is enabled, just like we do with the application. I'm not sure if we'd want to do that for all libraries, but if we do then it's actually easier than just doing it for oslo (we would configure the loggers more like what we're doing now in that mode).

3. We could ask the requests library maintainers to change the log level of the warning message (maybe we already have?), and we could set the level in the default_log_levels option, since we will still have that. If neither of those is sufficient, we could go further and insert a special log adapter for the requests library that intercepts that message and changes the log level. I think I would want a separate spec for that, though.'}, {'account_id': 6804, 'date': '2015-04-14 17:40:59.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Code-Review+1'}, {'account_id': 5638, 'date': '2015-04-27 16:11:59.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Workflow+1'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-04-27 16:12:05.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: -Verified

Starting gate jobs.
http://status.openstack.org/zuul/'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-04-27 16:19:45.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Verified+2

commit_message:
Allocate at least 5GB for Cloudera images

They install lots of packages, so make sure there's enough temporary
space for them.

Closes-bug: #1446925

Change-Id: I75c9f12fe42d4fbfc4d6f6f72a6cdcdb6af74aec

commit_message:
L2gw connection fails for invalid device/interface

Creating l2-gateway-connection gives internal
server error if invalid device or invalid interface
is specified.

Change-Id: I5a738b085400b3937dd4f03076233853d05133d0
Closes-bug: 1447467

commit_message:
Spec detailing Storm Scaling

Scaling a cluster is one of the benefits of using sahara to build
cluster. In order to use sahara at its best we need to implement this
feature for storm plugin.

Change-Id: Ibc24bf0c8f8b0fa5e62e303bf115910973ef7368
Implement: bp storm-scaling

commit_message:
Fix for missing id check in ACL count query.

Fixing issue and adding unit test to cover this API specifically.
It may need to be backported to Kilo as well.

Closes-Bug: #1447868

in order to implement security groups in OVN

Fix broken functional tests freezer_main()

Functional tests need to pass arguments directly to freezer_main()
as a regular dictionary.

Change-Id: I4ded66723ccb5f65d6f00415a8030917ce3c84ea
Implements: blueprint functional-testing

commit_message:
Add on-demand datasource polling

Previously every datasource pulled new data periodically, but
there was no way to ask the datasource to pull new data immediately.

This change adds an API call that causes the datasource to pull
new data immediately.

[{'created': '2015-02-26 00:05:02.000000000', 'message': "Router aren't being unscheduled when the last VM is deleted

When checking for ports that are still in use on a DVR outer,
the L3 agent scheduler makes the assumption that a port's
network must be owned by the same tenant. This isn't always
true as the admin could have created a shared network that
other tenants may use. The result of this assumption is that
the router associated with the shared network may not be
unscheduled from a VM host when the last VM (created by a
non-admin tenant) using the shared network is deleted from
the compute node.

This patch fixes this problem by using the admin credentials to
check for router port usage.

commit_message:
Router is not unscheduled when the last port is deleted

When checking for ports that are still in use on a DVR router,
the L3 agent scheduler makes the assumption that a port's
network must be owned by the same tenant. This isn't always
true as the admin could have created a shared network that
other tenants may use. The result of this assumption is that
the router associated with the shared network may not be
unscheduled from a VM host when the last VM (created by a
non-admin tenant) using the shared network is deleted from
the compute node.

The owner of a VM may not own all the ports of a shared
network.  Other tenants may have VMs using the same shared
network running on the same compute node. Also the VM owner
may not own the router ports. In order to check whether a
router can be unscheduled from a node has to be run with
admin context so all the ports associated with router are
returned from database queries.

This patch fixes this problem by using the admin context to
make the queries needed for the DVR scheduler to make the
correct unschedule decision.

Change-Id: I45477713d7ce16f2451fa6fbe04c610388b06867
Closes-bug: #1424096

commit_message:
Enable test_auth_token_middleware() on Python 2

Add python-memcached test dependency to Python 2 to run middleware tests
using memcache: test_auth_token_middleware().

python-memcached 1.54 doesn't support Python 3. I sent a pull request to
finish the port to Python 3.

Change-Id: I949630e121ba73385f2382f735005431c0bf004d

commit_message:
IBP: filter out block devices by MAJOR number

Since fuel-agent was switched to 'udevadm' database as a source of
block devices, it should apply filtering by MAJOR number when
searching for block devices occurs.

Change-Id: I009cb0b7b5be6cdf355d9ac524f0f925b61e62e9
Closes-Bug: #1449008

commit_message:
Initial import of ironic_discoverd_ramdisk

This is Python script for implementing a full-featured ironic-discoverd
ramdisk, including support for 'edeploy' plugin. It was initially
developed downstream.

Missing in this patch are:
* support for updating IPMI credentials
* support for serving logs via HTTP

Change-Id: I6987d46d7b6a1411d0d38f97373e5cd036ba6162
Implements: bluepring python-ramdisk-code

commit_message:
Support x-openstack-request-id

This patch aims to support "x-openstack-request-id" for Sahara.

Nova, Cinder and Neutron have realized
"x-openstack-request-id" functionality.
This functionality will enable effective log tracing.

Change-Id: If0a0b10145d85eff811cdd2114f73494ae7e324a

commit_message:
Adjust registration of ami image in boto tests

Adjust registration of ami image in boto tests to be compatible with
stackforge ec2api.

This change set kernel_id and ramdisk_id properties of an ami image. As
a result the image could be used to run an instance without specifying
of these additional images.

Nova EC2 doesn't support set of these attributes in register image
operation (LP #954335). So a run operation must specify both of them.
Ec2api doesn't support specifying these in run operation (LP #1441138).
So registration of ami image must set both of them.

Now both requirements are satisfied, thus this testcase should work
properly for both Nova EC2 and ec2api.

Change-Id: I36ef88a561e60fb5dc3e687cb8bc02b27ec2e814

Hey Jeff: I just spent a bit of time thinking about this and I'm not sure this is what we want to do, yet. I see where you're going with this and in fact I opened+closed a similar review [1] when we were still working out which params were missing.


This problem arises because of a difference between the 'master' template used for deployment of overcloud using tuskar or not [2]. Without tuskar we use the raw 'overcloud-without-mergepy.yaml' so defaults defined there for these parameters are in play. With tuskar we use the generated plan.yaml and this only includes the role-specific params (like Compute-1::NeutronBridgeMapping). 

One unanswered question for me is what/how is tuskar parsing the master-seed and role templates to generate plan.yaml, in such a way that we lose the default definitions from overcloud-without-mergepy.yaml

As a side note, looking around, from [3] it seems like putting global parameter defaults into environment.yaml is a better way of enforcing them (I only mention due to the relevance of setting defaults, and because I came across it, I don't think it is part of the solution at this point anyway)

[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/168843/
[2] https://github.com/rdo-management/instack-undercloud/blob/master/scripts/instack-deploy-overcloud#L233
[3] http://docs.openstack.org/developer/heat/template_guide/environment.html"}, {'account_id': 6928, 'date': '2015-04-08 16:10:17.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

This is something that has bothered me for a while.  I'd really like to reduce the amount of duplicated defaults we have.  I've added a topic to the summit session etherpad to discuss.

Related to this specific change, are these neutron defaults something that would be generally applicable to someone who wanted to use the templates in a non-devtest environment?  If not, maybe we should just remove the template defaults entirely.  It's not as if a value of '' is useful to anyone anyway, so clearly the defaults had to be overridden anyway."}, {'account_id': 8449, 'date': '2015-04-09 14:54:10.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2: Code-Review+1

OK, thanks Jeff for irc discussion - i think we agree (and also from Ben's comments) that there is inconsistency in parameter defaults in the tripleo-heat-templates. If these were enforced globally via an environment file, it would be easier/possible for Tuskar to grab them as that is always present - in any case and especially since there is a plan for a dedicated summit session to discuss that change, we could/should land this as a fix for the tuskar puppet deploy for now."}, {'account_id': 3098, 'date': '2015-04-09 16:09:58.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

This change isn't required for Tuskar deploy, so don't let that motivation change your view of this change. This merely changes the templates to be consistent. There are other parameters that the default already match, but if there are definitely long term plans to clean all this up that's fine. As far as the Neutron parameter defaults go with being set to a blank string (or any of them really), I doubt it helps much but I can't say for sure. Updating the review with the non-puppet templates changed."}, {'account_id': 3098, 'date': '2015-04-09 16:10:42.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 3.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-04-09 16:15:36.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Verified+1

>  I'd really like to reduce the amount of duplicated defaults we have. 

One option is to move towards using parameter_defaults in the environment for all defaults, e.g remove *all* defaults from the templates themselves.

This would have the side benefit of removing the "plumbing" where parameters are passed down through multiple layers of nested template.

The only downside of the parameter_defaults approach is you'd need to be careful with parameter naming to avoid conflicts/collisions in nested templates, I assume some namespacing e.g a naming convention can solve this though.

http://docs.openstack.org/developer/heat/template_guide/environment.html#define-defaults-to-parameters

https://github.com/openstack/tripleo-heat-templates/blob/master/overcloud-resource-registry-puppet.yaml#L20

I'm +1 on at least making the defaults that exist now consistent though, regardless of any future cleanup which may happen.'}, {'account_id': 6796, 'date': '2015-04-16 14:47:36.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

commit_message:
Make all default values match overcloud defaults

It's very confusing for them to be different, especially in the case of
comparing Tuskar vs non-Tuskar deployments where the parameters are read
from different files.

Note: NeutronPhysicalBridge is named differently in the overcloud
template (HypervisorNeutronPhysicalBridge). This is the only parameter
checked that isn't named exactly the same, hopefully there aren't any
others.

(Checked controller, compute, ceph, cinder, and swift for both puppet
and non-puppet templates)

Change-Id: I48ce1eb40d2d080c589ce619c50eddff17efe882

commit_message:
Separate the network configuration per flavor.

This change allows a different network config for each family of hosts. For
instance, the controller may have a different network configuration than a
block storage node. This change adds a declaration for each family in the
overcloud-resource-registry.yaml & overcloud-resource-registry-puppet.yaml.

Change-Id: I083df7ebbb535f97d8ddec2ac0e06281c55986cd

commit_message:
Cleanup some details about the accounts files

This commit cleans up some details in the accounts.yaml sample file
and the tempest configuration guide to provide missing details about
how to create and use an accounts file. Specifically it adds more
detailed comments to the sample file about each section, and in the
config guide it removes obsolete sections and adds some missing
details.

Change-Id: Ic11335fe1215ab0625ea2308ccc75d22a284c432
Closes-Bug: #1447851

commit_message:
Fix non-locking test accounts doc section

This commit fixes several issues with the non-locking cred provider
section in the tempest config guide. It was in a state stuck between
refactors and didn't accurately describe how it should be used anymore.

commit_message:
Add a paragraph on the use of tempest_roles option

This commit adds a paragraph to the tempest configuration guide on how
to use the tempest_roles option. This was previously missing from the
tenant isolation section.

Change-Id: I1ef1649186edbeb51e1ced1bbb361b78eaef3721

commit_message:
Switch all uses of StringIO to use it from six

As part of enabling python3 support in tempest we need to be able to
handle StringIO usage in both python2 and python3. Six provides a
compat layer for doing this, so this commit moves all uses of StringIO
and cStringIO to get it through six.

Change-Id: Ie6ac86b3b5ed2c307dc2cc41386da9e5ba1ee23e

commit_message:
Set of fixes for patching tests

 * Add additional options to `apt-get`, so it resolves
configuration file conflicts without running conffile
prompt.
 * Add logging of repositories parsing.
 * Skip tests if target from erratum doesn't match tests
target and return '123' exit code.
 * Always use only RPM packages from erratum and
CentOS mirrors during tests for master node patching.
 * Do not fail tests if there are no updates for master
node (temporary) in order to test patching of packages
which are installed inside Docker containers.

Change-Id: I8351d05b74391f3916119462f1541285d2be756a
Implements: blueprint mos-patching-tests

Add tftp configuration for ironic

Expose the tftp configuration to support tftp, disable by default.

Closes-bug: #1446972

commit_message:
Minor fixes for docker troubleshooting

Fixed some syntactical mistakes as well as
added an alternative way to find container ID
for corrupted containers.

Change-Id: Iae544e73de4c2b094115b652de1f6b55c0a35f4c
Closes-Bug: #1446274

commit_message:
Make script executable and BSD sed compatible

This patch sets the sources-branch-updater script to be executable and adjusts
the in-place sed operation to work for both GNU sed and BSD sed.

Partially implements: blueprint master-kilofication
