revisions:
[{'created': '2015-04-22 00:06:59.000000000', 'message': 'Fix the package pinning problem within the galera roles

The package pinning issue in galera is related to how the perf file
or the lack there of is being created. The perf file for apt pinning
needs to be locked down to the domain which is providing the extra
packages. To accomplish this a filter plugin was created to parse
a url and allow for the perf template file to be effectively
instructing apt to prefer packages from the extra repository over
anything else.

Closes-Bug: 1446772

Change-Id: I503054e27425231b1d40a695786f8ce049f78d53

The package pinning issue in galera is related to how the pref file
or the lack there of is being created. The pref file for apt pinning
needs to be locked down to the release organisation which is providing
the extra packages.

A filter plugin was added to allow for a url to be parsed for the
purpose of pinning to an origin.

The PPA being used for modern rsyslog is exhibiting signs that its
prone to failure. Upon further review the V8 stable PPA is tied

commit_message:
Fix the package pinning problem within the roles

The package pinning issue in galera is related to how the pref file
or the lack there of is being created. The pref file for apt pinning
needs to be locked down to the release organisation which is providing
the extra packages.

A filter plugin was added to allow for a url to be parsed for the
purpose of pinning to an origin.

This is the recommended solution per the upstream mariadb
documentation as found here:
https://mariadb.com/kb/en/mariadb/installing-mariadb-deb-files/

The PPA being used for modern rsyslog is exhibiting signs that its
prone to failure. Upon further review the V8 stable PPA is tied
directly to launchpad which is a known failure domain. To correct
this issue the PPA was removed and the additional repo from within
the rsyslog_* roles was made optional.

The base image appears to have a package that conflicts with MariaDB packages,
so the AIO bootstrap script is set to remove the conflicting packages.

Partially implements: blueprint master-kilofication

Closes-Bug: #1446772
Change-Id: I503054e27425231b1d40a695786f8ce049f78d53

commit_message:
Run docker containers with explicit version

Supervisor should start containers based on the
version of Fuel, not specific to dockerctl. This
will alleviate some issues with container versioning
during upgrade and rollback of Fuel Master.

Change-Id: Ia839cc2aa4e584b7b01793a5738f6542b9a07c8e
Related-Bug: #1446075
Closes-Bug: #1447567

commit_message:
Delete PHP Zend Server app from murano-apps repository

Since Docker implementation of Zend Server is a preview, developers
include a time limited license with it.
Murano-apps repository includes apps which can work immediately
out of box and supporting of license essentially restricts this
ability. So, this app must be deleted.

Change-Id: I70ee12d7d4fa3ec307324b9019bc57ab54903a44
Closes-Bug: #1445087

commit_message:
Delete PHP Zend Server app from murano-apps repository

Since Docker implementation of Zend Server is a preview, developers
include a time limited license with it.
Murano-apps repository includes apps which can work immediately
out of box and supporting of license essentially restricts this
ability. So, this app must be deleted.

Change-Id: I70ee12d7d4fa3ec307324b9019bc57ab54903a44
Closes-Bug: #1445087

[{'created': '2015-04-24 09:43:17.000000000', 'message': "Bump kombu version and add amqp version

oslo.messaging now implements rabbitmq heartbeat.

py-amqp (the underlying low library to connect to rabbitmq) has a
working support of heartbeat since 1.4.0. So we need at least
that version.

Given that Trusty has 3.0.7 of kombu and the authors have indicated
that amqp>=1.3.3,<2.0 would work with that version, we can use
amqp 1.4.0 with kombu 3.0.7.

So this change raises the kombu requirement to '>=3.0.7' and
amqp to '>=1.4.0'

Change-Id: I2b111af06e27caf1436cbda2de5be547c7d8790c
Closes-bug: #1436769
(cherry picked from commit c7f69afd6af56e8f7956c6fa0bea8fd776151fe6)
"}]
commit_message:
Bump kombu version and add amqp version

oslo.messaging now implements rabbitmq heartbeat.

py-amqp (the underlying low library to connect to rabbitmq) has a
working support of heartbeat since 1.4.0. So we need at least
that version.

Given that Trusty has 3.0.7 of kombu and the authors have indicated
that amqp>=1.3.3,<2.0 would work with that version, we can use
amqp 1.4.0 with kombu 3.0.7.

So this change raises the kombu requirement to '>=3.0.7' and
amqp to '>=1.4.0'

Change-Id: I2b111af06e27caf1436cbda2de5be547c7d8790c
Closes-bug: #1436769
(cherry picked from commit c7f69afd6af56e8f7956c6fa0bea8fd776151fe6)

commit_message:
Using senlin endpoint url to create webhook url

Currently, the webhook url is generated based on the host and port
that senlin api is listening to. This is incorrect. This patch fixed
this issue by querying senlin endpoint service and using its url to
generate webhook url.

Change-Id: I2fd17006e767010aa281b5d9ffafa9be63ebf612

commit_message:
Fix project-config post jobs

We cannot limit post jobs with files a section, they will never run.

Remove the post jobs from the condition.

Change-Id: I3c720f03197620629f3d03dce0978f8d8cd25468

commit_message:
Honour new test variable PIPVERSION

This allows testing with unreleased pips, which is important to know
if something is going to cause us or our users trouble.

Change-Id: Icb3a9c1486c76b673d25a3d18792baad3d26c763

Dan,

The initial purpose of the work done here is to rely on puppet classes directly and avoid yet another composition layer (puppet-tripleo).

For loadbalancer it has been done this way since it didn't seem we could do it in another way, but here we can definitely do it sticking to include class without much changes.

On a later iteration we should split the .pp file in its own specialized service (ie. overcloud_mysql.pp, overcloud_rabbit.pp), but for the galera case I don't think that relying on puppet-tripleo is worth it/necessary."}, {'account_id': 3153, 'date': '2015-04-01 19:08:28.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 8: Code-Review+1'}, {'account_id': 360, 'date': '2015-04-01 19:19:50.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 8: Code-Review+2'}, {'account_id': 9410, 'date': '2015-04-01 19:24:10.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 8: Workflow-1'}, {'account_id': 9410, 'date': '2015-04-04 17:12:15.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 9.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-04-04 17:12:21.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 9: Verified+1

commit_message:
galera: Allow installer to setup galera cluster

This commit aims to allow the installer to setup a galera cluster.

Decision is made based on the number of controller nodes.
The systemd unit file of the master is overriden to add
--wsrep-new-cluster.

Co-Authored-By: Giulio Fidente <gfidente@redhat.com>

Change-Id: Iff85659bf5cfc8a4fe1bce89e7b91a9589e00a71
Depends-On: Idfd72de4fafdce2a9c16945961fee996a98049b7
Depends-On: I06b669123fe08e02c66ee34dab78a943ff5de90c
Depends-On: Iec31d724370a40aee56ead5839ef47ceacf7223d
Depends-On: I4ff0512a0d15ac4797c8c64ed76c0fd3fc31b45c

commit_message:
Deprecate v1.1 and remove v3

Module novaclient.v1_1 is already deprecated, so it's time to stop using it
inside novaclient.

Since support of v3 nova is undocumented feature, which uses v2
implementation, we can remove code related to it.

Also, this patch removes redundant check for compute api version != 1.0.

Change-Id: I06b349f704d5ae2c592d8d286da268870f2a69e9

commit_message:
Jshint unused and undef cleanup for networktopology JS

Removing unused and undefined variables in networktopology javascript.
This ensures that once we enable it globally, the gate will not barf.

Change-Id: Ia071199aef0f65fb56fe70475e8a47f89d8f9084
Partial-Bug: #1438620

[{'created': '2015-03-30 15:21:56.000000000', 'message': "Support platform-specific requirements files

This patch adds support for choosing a requirements file, based on the
current OS, with the format 'requirements-{osname}'. This can be combined
with the current approach of choosing a requirement file based on the
Python version. The motivation for this is to replace conditional
choosing of packages inside setup.py.

Change-Id: I30c56082bb9b9bcd80128eedcef17b6beb793cf8
(cherry picked from commit 8cdb41cf1264e71fd2f479efa7decd38c1f91cfa)
"}]
commit_message:
Support platform-specific requirements files

This patch adds support for choosing a requirements file, based on the
current OS, with the format 'requirements-{osname}'. This can be combined
with the current approach of choosing a requirement file based on the
Python version. The motivation for this is to replace conditional
choosing of packages inside setup.py.

Change-Id: I30c56082bb9b9bcd80128eedcef17b6beb793cf8
(cherry picked from commit 8cdb41cf1264e71fd2f479efa7decd38c1f91cfa)

commit_message:
Avoid indexing into an empty list in getcallargs

If a method signature has no named arguments, either empty or
(*args, **kwargs), then inspect.getargspec() will return an empty list
for argnames.  In that case we should not try to compare against the
first element of that list.

Also updates the docstring for getcallargs to specify a limitation of
the method.

Change-Id: I68af587fe91310a68bb5c37b80d3f00f5d45dd16

commit_message:
Update rpc version aliases for kilo

Update all of the rpc client API classes to include a version alias
for the latest version implemented in Kilo.  This alias is needed when
doing rolling upgrades from Kilo to Liberty.  With this in place, you can
ensure all services only send messages that both Kilo and Liberty will
understand.

Change-Id: I2952aec9aae747639aa519af55fb5fa25b8f3ab4
Closes-Bug: #1444745

commit_message:
Support both list and dict for pci_passthrough_whitelist

In Icehouse, pci_passthrough_whitelist is a json docstring that
encodes a list. In Juno, it is a json docstring that encodes
a dict. This patch adds the list support back to
pci_passthrough_whitelist, and both list and dict are now supported.

(cherry picked from commit bb7bfd313c9d4c052c85b4ad5ccd8361f5f3b004)

Conflicts:
	nova/pci/pci_whitelist.py
	nova/tests/pci/test_pci_devspec.py
Because juno imports module as pci_devspec since
kilo as devspec.

Closes-Bug: 1383345
Change-Id: I523cfb756a09c75e4f60015adadb3a1403298cd3

https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/ThirdPartySystems/NetApp_CI'}, {'account_id': 10115, 'date': '2015-04-21 19:07:18.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

Can you explain more detail of your problem? I'm not sure why this backport patch is needed.

When c-vol re-export the volume via systemctl restart openstack-cinder-volume, ensure_export() is called in Juno. This reuses username and password getting from database.
I tried re-export using RHEL OSP6 with lioadm, I didn't any problem by restarting c-vol service."}, {'account_id': 9555, 'date': '2015-04-22 08:39:02.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

The problem occurs during live migration. It may also occur during other operations.

When the Nova libvirt driver calls initialize_connection on the destination host, this results in a call to the cinder driver's create_export, which is defined in _ExportMixin. This calls _get_target_chap_auth() to get the current credentials. In the case of LioAdm without this backport, this returns None, which results in new credentials being created. The existing credentials are overwritten with the invalid credentials, resulting in an inaccessible volume. The migration fails."}, {'account_id': 9555, 'date': '2015-04-22 09:32:59.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

It's worth saying again that this is a backport of change Iea3d94e35a4ced4dafc1b61e2df6b075cf200577 , btw. It's just not a straightforward backport due to surrounding refactoring, and the change in question being badly scoped. This isn't new code."}, {'account_id': 10115, 'date': '2015-04-23 18:31:27.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

Hi Matthew,

Based on the discussion on IRC, I understood your problem.

The problem happens when the VM is back to Host A from B via live-migrate after once live-migrate from Host A to B.

First live-migrate(A->B) doesn't have any problem but second live-migrate(B->A) causes "no iscsi session" error due to credential error.

I think this fix is right solution for this problem.'}, {'account_id': 7198, 'date': '2015-04-23 18:44:50.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3: Code-Review+2

Matthew,

My apologies.  You did explain why there was no cherry-pick info in the commit.  For some reason that didn't parse when I last looked through this.

If the original commit is poorly scoped and this resolves the bug with the smallest possible bit, this looks like the right way to go then.

Thanks."}, {'account_id': 10115, 'date': '2015-04-23 18:47:53.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Code-Review+1'}, {'account_id': 979, 'date': '2015-04-27 10:17:19.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Code-Review+2 Workflow+1'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-04-27 10:17:24.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: -Verified

commit_message:
Fix re-export of iscsi volume when using lioadm

This change ensures we check for existing chap credentials in the db
when re-exporting a volume. Without this change we overwrite the
existing credentials, resulting in an inaccessible volume.

This is a manual cut and paste of portions of change
Iea3d94e35a4ced4dafc1b61e2df6b075cf200577. Specifically, we add the
overridden _get_target_chap_auth for LioAdm, and add a context
argument to the function throughout.

It is not possible or desirable to backport the whole change for several
reasons:

* It is based on a refactor which is not on this branch
* It includes a refactor which is not relevant to this branch
* It includes more than 1 fix

Closes-bug: #1410566
Change-Id: I9859306b8beb0e1d8e3b3f6464c3f42e672e3949

commit_message:
MidoNet's Neutron client to StackForge

Neutron client now allows to be extended via external projects:
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/148318/.

Create MidoNet's Neutron client into StackForge to superseed
`python-neutronclient` and define MidoNet extension commands.

We would like to use the same gerrit acls group config as
`networking-midonet`, so
`gerrit/acls/stackforge/networking-midonet-client.config` is not created
and `networking-midonet.config` is  mentioned in `gerrit/projects.yaml`

Change-Id: I83577d958914d0167df8da2a5a3d1d6ddb858480

commit_message:
Avoid using a thread local token storage

When one thread is running the coordinator heartbeat()
periodically and another is using the lock(s) it should
be possible to correctly make this happen/work without
errors of the type of:

AttributeError: '_thread._local' object has no
                attribute 'token'

This happens because the coordinator heartbeat() method
calls into each current lock(s) heartbeat()
method (which then extends the lock via the locks
extend() method); when this is using thread local storage
this fails with the above error.

So to avoid this explicitly disallow using thread
local token storage by ensuring we pass in the right param
to the underlying redis lock.

Change-Id: I8e5592813577c3cf1cf9a67d0005d1e0ef180fca

skips step to change it, application will not work

revisions:
[{'created': '2015-04-27 08:37:37.000000000', 'message': 'Change dragonflow commit type

The current scheme of "Merge if necessary" creates a convoluted history
that you can't effectively use bisect or blame on.

Git log is becomes useless as it shows a mix of merge and FF commits.
Example:
  ea577bb Merge "Normalize projects.yaml"
  be66f7f Merge "Change Magnum's bandit gate"
  ea77167 Normalize projects.yaml

Git show doesn't work on most of the history:
Example:
$ git show ea577bb
commit ea577bbf3650a2b0c1ed76d2f94fea336da23cd8
Merge: be66f7f ea77167
Author: Jenkins <jenkins@review.openstack.org>
Date:   Thu Apr 23 07:10:15 2015 +0000

    Merge "Normalize projects.yaml"

<<NOTICE NO DIFF>>

Also add the fact that git blame dates get displayed out of order on you
get a whole soup of git mess.

Merge commits only work if the maintainers takes care of merging whole
features at once and only use merges. Gerrit doesn't work that way and
parts of features get interleaved. This means that by using merge
commits you effectively make the git history unhelpful and the git tree
a confusing mess. Moving to cherry-pick or ff-only fixes those issues
and creates a clean definitive history for the master branch.

We choose ff-only as the project is in it's early state so things are
changing rapidly and we don't have many automated tests so we prefer
that developers manually rebase and retest changes before we can commit
them. In the future we will probably move to a cherry-pick model so that
trivial merges are done on the server and don't require a new patch-set.

Change-Id: I4877e30de53dcaa211be6b62daefed5d1f355d6e
Signed-off-by: Saggi Mizrahi <saggi.mizrahi@huawei.com>
'}]
commit_message:
Change dragonflow commit type

The current scheme of "Merge if necessary" creates a convoluted history
that you can't effectively use bisect or blame on.

Git log is becomes useless as it shows a mix of merge and FF commits.
Example:
  ea577bb Merge "Normalize projects.yaml"
  be66f7f Merge "Change Magnum's bandit gate"
  ea77167 Normalize projects.yaml

Git show doesn't work on most of the history:
Example:
$ git show ea577bb
commit ea577bbf3650a2b0c1ed76d2f94fea336da23cd8
Merge: be66f7f ea77167
Author: Jenkins <jenkins@review.openstack.org>
Date:   Thu Apr 23 07:10:15 2015 +0000

    Merge "Normalize projects.yaml"

<<NOTICE NO DIFF>>

Also add the fact that git blame dates get displayed out of order on you
get a whole soup of git mess.

Merge commits only work if the maintainers takes care of merging whole
features at once and only use merges. Gerrit doesn't work that way and
parts of features get interleaved. This means that by using merge
commits you effectively make the git history unhelpful and the git tree
a confusing mess. Moving to cherry-pick or ff-only fixes those issues
and creates a clean definitive history for the master branch.

We choose ff-only as the project is in it's early state so things are
changing rapidly and we don't have many automated tests so we prefer
that developers manually rebase and retest changes before we can commit
them. In the future we will probably move to a cherry-pick model so that
trivial merges are done on the server and don't require a new patch-set.

Change-Id: I4877e30de53dcaa211be6b62daefed5d1f355d6e
Signed-off-by: Saggi Mizrahi <saggi.mizrahi@huawei.com>

commit_message:
Enforce alphabetic loading order for --config-dir contents

Deployers may want to rely on specific order of the files being loaded,
so we should make sure it's not changed, and that it's documented.

Note: test_config_dir already checks for the sorting order of
configuration files, so there is no need for a new test case.

Change-Id: Idc26b926601554b5592e13da92fbe81db99eb6e0

commit_message:
Add Python 3 classifiers to setup.cfg

Add Python 3, 3.3 and 3.4 classifiers. The "Python :: 3" classifier is
needed by the caniusepython3 tool to check if dependencies of a project
are Python 3 compatible:

    https://caniusepython3.com/

Information on the Python 3 port of OpenStack:

    https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/Python3

Change-Id: I2a0c8d7c3ab3c97a945a49b64a56341c35ec5536

Just because Swift takes advantage of SSH, does not mean that SSH should be managed within the Swift module. Using that same logic, we should also manage Python, package repositories, SSH keys, etc.

As I mention in my commit, SSH is such a low-level service (from an operators perspective) that if they are using Puppet to deploy production infrastructure, there is a high probability that they are already managing SSH.

Furthermore, I believe there is an increased likelihood of confusion on the part of the user. Personally, I would never expect a module built for configuring OpenStack Swift would also have a hand in configuring SSH - I expect that it would be called out as a pre-requisite to getting started with the module.'}, {'account_id': 14496, 'date': '2015-04-23 17:07:07.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Code-Review+1

commit_message:
Removal of SSH Components

This change removes all SSH-related components, their configuration
options, and tests.

SSH is such a low-level service (from the perspective of any operator
deploying a cloud), that it is reasonable to assume that (or provide
direction that) SSH must be installed and configured prior to usage of
the puppet-swift module.

Without this change, there is a significant liklihood of confusion
occurring in the likely case of SSH being managed elsewhere.

Change-Id: I0f695788b2784669a3fb285e4bedf0159c4cb89a
Closes-Bug: 1447259

commit_message:
Add the 'traits' parameter to pypowervm Response

A recent commit in pypowervm now requires a 'traits' parameter
to be specified on a Response object. Updated the unit tests
to supply 'None' since traits are not used in the testing.

Change-Id: I2272bb55b4575374ba93c77222531a9ce71afb3e

commit_message:
Support feature/development for askbot-theme

Add merge commit control for a new askbot-theme-release group,
switch tag permissions to that group as well, and add the
feature/development branch to the list of branches gerritbot will
report on.

Change-Id: I5a0f3473e16a8df29b7514b61fff3651b9a151c6

commit_message:
mkrepo.sh: download base packages properly.

Skip the epoch in the packages' file names in order to not confuse
debootstrap (which fails if the deb package file name contains the colon
character). In order to avoid the problem download the base packages
in the same manners as others instead of copying them from multistrap
cache (it's multistrap which modifies the packages' file names).

Partial-Bug: #1441611
Change-Id: Ib5b857a0ae637cc5c327e45f28e8397ae000b78f

subject: force arch amd64 for EL7 elements
revisions:
[{'created': '2015-04-27 12:09:37.000000000', 'message': 'force arch amd64 for EL7 elements

rhel7 and centos7 images are both only available on x86_64 arch.
if $ARCH is misconfigured, some strange error will happen during the build.
For example, DIB will try to install EPEL i386 on the 64bit root system.

For the record, tripleo-incubator $NODE_ARCH default value is i386. The
problem will happend as soon as the default value is used with one of
these root elements.

This commit ensure the $ARCH is set to amd64 as soon as the centos7 or
rhel7 root element are used.

Change-Id: Id62c85be30fdb14290b8096657391825b00e255d
'}]
commit_message:
force arch amd64 for EL7 elements

rhel7 and centos7 images are both only available on x86_64 arch.
if $ARCH is misconfigured, some strange error will happen during the build.
For example, DIB will try to install EPEL i386 on the 64bit root system.

For the record, tripleo-incubator $NODE_ARCH default value is i386. The
problem will happend as soon as the default value is used with one of
these root elements.

This commit ensure the $ARCH is set to amd64 as soon as the centos7 or
rhel7 root element are used.

Change-Id: Id62c85be30fdb14290b8096657391825b00e255d
